SIMPLE: madden
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madden
<hw>Mad"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Maddened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Maddening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
mad; to drive to madness; to drive to insanity; to craze.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make very angry; to enrage; to excite violently
with passion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Madden
<hw>Mad"den</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become mad; to act as if
mad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They rave, recite, and <qex>madden</qex> round the land.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maddened</ent>⟦br⟧
